title: Lake Roosevelt National Recreation Area: Project: Wild Salmon
body: Project: Wild Salmon       3rd-12th  This kit is the Washington Department of Fish and Wildlife's Project WILD Salmon Education Trunk of educational activities. It is filled with resources and materials about salmon, including: books, videos, puppets, and preserved sample life cycle of salmon.  NOTE: This trunk is very heavy. It is only available for pick up and delivery within the Lake Roosevelt area. Contact our education specialist for more information or to reserve this trunk.
